            <h2>Understanding the Catechism of the Catholic Church</h2>

            <h3>What is the Catechism?</h3>
            <p>The Catechism of the Catholic Church (CCC) is a summary of Catholic beliefs, including teachings on the Trinity, sacraments, morality, and prayer.</p>

            <h3>Four Pillars of the Catechism</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>The Creed</strong>: What Catholics believe.</li>
                <li><strong>The Sacraments</strong>: How Catholics worship.</li>
                <li><strong>Morality</strong>: How Catholics should live.</li>
                <li><strong>Prayer</strong>: The importance of communicating with God.</li>
            </ul>

            <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/lpkMtlkrzoA" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
